Gallery: Gretchen Carlson, Miss America 1989, as she looked when she was With the Greater Twin Cities Youth Symphonies. As a teen-ager from Anoka, Carlson won several state and national awards as a violinist, as well as a scholarship to the Juilliard School of Music in New York, and was a soloist with the Minnesota Orchestra.
